-- Gulf Finance House Third-Quarter Loss Widens to $115 Million on Bad Loans
-- B y   A y e s h a   D a y a
-- 2010-10-27T04:12:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/gulf-finance-house-third-quarter-loss-widens-to-115-million-on-bad-loans.html
Gulf Finance House EC, the Bahrain-
based investment bank, said third-quarter loss widened to $115.1
million from $29.3 million a year earlier as it set aside money
to cover bad loans.  Impairment allowance for the third-quarter was $81.5
million, the bank said in a statement to the Dubai bourse today.
Gulf Finance House shares are listed in Dubai, Kuwait and
Bahrain bourses.  To contact the reporter on this story:
